---
import Atlas from "../layouts/Atlas.astro";
---

<Atlas
  title="Developers — Worldbuilders public API"
  description="Public read-only tile manifest API, OSS Roblox emitter, and schema docs for Worldbuilders."
>
  <section class="wrap lat-band" data-lat="LAT BAND 62°N · developers">
    <p class="eyebrow">For builders</p>
    <h1>Build on <span class="text-aurora">Worldbuilders</span>.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A read-only public API, an OSS Roblox emitter (MIT), and a manifest
      schema that&rsquo;s the single source of truth for both the in-game
      and web renderers. The shape below is what HttpService receives —
      identical to what the Astro renderer uses to draw mini-tiles.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap lat-band" data-lat="LAT BAND 62°N · tile manifest">
    <p class="eyebrow">GET /v1/tile/&#123;z&#125;/&#123;x&#125;/&#123;y&#125;</p>
    <h2>The tile manifest</h2>
    <p>
      Slippy-map XYZ coordinates in, JSON manifest out. Signed with HMAC,
      cached at the edge for 60&nbsp;s. Studs are rebased to the tile&rsquo;s
      local origin; coordinates round-trip via <code>center_wgs84</code>.
    </p>
    <pre class="code"><code>{`{
  "manifest_version": "1.0",
  "style_version": 1,
  "tile":  { "z": 16, "x": 33887, "y": 18095 },
  "stud_scale": 2.0,
  "center_wgs84": [62.4730, 6.1496],
  "region_key": "NO_rural_subarctic",
  "buildings": [
    {
      "osm_id": "way/227908624",
      "footprint_studs": [[483.98, -18.86], ...],
      "height_studs": 14.5,
      "kind": "restaurant"
    }
  ],
  "roads":     [...],
  "water":     [...],
  "terrain":   { "grid_size": 64, "heights": [...] }
}`}</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap lat-band" data-lat="LAT BAND 62°N · endpoints">
    <p class="eyebrow">Endpoints · public · read-only</p>
    <table class="endpoints">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Status</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="mono">GET</td>
          <td class="mono">/v1/tile/&#123;z&#125;/&#123;x&#125;/&#123;y&#125;</td>
          <td>Baked tile manifest</td>
          <td><span class="status status-live">live</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="mono">GET</td>
          <td class="mono">/v1/leaderboard</td>
          <td>Top plots · 60&thinsp;s cache</td>
          <td><span class="status status-soon">Q443</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="mono">GET</td>
          <td class="mono">/v1/openapi.json</td>
          <td>OpenAPI 3.1 spec</td>
          <td><span class="status status-soon">Q327</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="mono">GET</td>
          <td class="mono">/v1/region/&#123;key&#125;</td>
          <td>Region metadata + tiling bbox</td>
          <td><span class="status status-soon">Q443</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap lat-band" data-lat="LAT BAND 62°N · OSS">
    <p class="eyebrow">Open source</p>
    <h2>The Roblox emitter, in the open.</h2>
    <p>
      The bake itself is a fork of <code>louis-e/arnis</code> with a new
      <code>roblox_emitter</code> module. Source goes public the day the
      Astro renderer hits perf budget. MIT-licensed; PRs welcome.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href="https://github.com/worldbuilders" class="btn-ghost">github.com/worldbuilders</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</Atlas>

<style>
  .lede { color: var(--fg-soft); font-size: 1.04rem; max-width: 64ch; }
  .code {
    margin: 1.6rem 0 0;
    padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--color-aurora-green);
    overflow-x: auto;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }
  .code code { font-family: var(--font-mono); color: var(--fg); }
  .endpoints {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin-top: 1.6rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
  }
  .endpoints th, .endpoints td {
    text-align: left;
    padding: 0.9rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .endpoints th {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--fg-faint);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .endpoints td.mono { font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .status {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.66rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    border-radius: 999px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .status-live {
    color: var(--color-aurora-green);
    border-color: var(--color-aurora-green);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(91, 233, 185, 0.25);
  }
  .status-soon {
    color: var(--color-aurora-amber);
    border-color: var(--color-aurora-amber);
  }
  .text-aurora { color: var(--color-aurora-green); }
</style>
